				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Training trap and lock skills<a name="51043"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 10 04 2:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I just tried to train sense traps at the guild hall--definitely capped at 63 for level 21; the same is true for picklock (63 at level 21). In both cases the GM told me &quot;You are already trained to the limit of your abilities&quot; </span></blockquote>
<br />
The GM at the guild hall was not a guide, he was a Guild Master NPC, and I have never known them to be mistaken about game mechanics. The response I got is the one that one gets when trying to train above the current level cap. And it wasn't due to lack of points (40 left) or cash on hand.
<br />

<br />
I didn't bother mentioning the skills page because it doesn't contain the per-level cap info and is out of date anyway. (pick lock trains at level 10 for sure, sense traps at level 15, and disarm traps at level 20).
<br />

<br />
I am assuming that although it was (level+1)*5 originally, it was changed for LDoN to give rogues a bit of an edge in dealing with traps.
<br />

<br />
And, yes, I had already practiced up to 63 on the elevator lock in Paneil before going to the guild hall. I only noticed the plateau on disarm and pick locks after having trained them up in the first place.
<br />

<br />
/Aside on
<br />
I was somewhat taken aback by how negative the responses to my question were. Rather than accepting that I had noticed something of interest in the game, the responders' tone seemed to indicate that I must have made a mistake, or perhaps that my input is worthless given all the historical information lying around on the site.
<br />

<br />
Am I to assume from this that new contributions by younger bards are not appreciated.
<br />
/Aside off
<br />

<br />
I will post more information on this thread as I get more data points.
<br />

<br />
[edit]New data:
<br />
Level 22 max sense traps and pick lock 66
<br />
Level 23 max sense traps and pick lock 69
<br />
(Disarm traps going at the normal Level*5+5)
<br />

